$ op-reg-at.pl

A → development/languages/Perl[Perl] script to open the → Windows/registry[windows registry] with → Windows/dirs/Windows/regedit_exe[`regedit.exe`] at a particular
→ Windows/registry/tree-structure/key[registry key].

The script is used like so:
code {
c:\> op-reg-at.pl HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced
code }

{ op-reg-at.pl

  gh|scripts-and-utilities|/op-reg-at.pl||

}

sa:

  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion/Applets/Regedit/LastKey[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Applets\Regedit: LastKey]

  → development/tools/scripts/personal/regat_bat[`regat.bat`]: a → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[`cmd.exe`] batch file that does the same thing.

  → development/languages/Perl/modules/Win32/TieRegistry

  → development/tools/scripts/personal/[Scripts]
